turn.2: Alice's Shop Alice's Shop is a shop at 83 St Aldate's, Oxford, England.
turn.3: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.4: With 82 St Aldate's next door it is part of a stone-built 15th-century house that was remodelled in the 17th century.
turn.6: It is now a gift shop selling gifts, souvenirs and memorabilia, all based on Alice.
turn.8: 83 St Aldate's has long been a shop.
turn.10: In the Victorian era its customers included Alice Liddell, daughter of Henry Liddell, who was Dean of Christ Church, Oxford, which is opposite the shop.
turn.12: Alice, who used to buy sweets at the shop, was the inspiration for Lewis Carroll's "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland" and "Through the Looking-Glass".
